Taxes.
Any and all payments by or on behalf of a Credit Party hereunder or under the other Loan Documents shall be made, in accordance with this , free and clear of and without deduction for any and all present or future Taxes, (excluding Taxes imposed on or measured by the net income or capital of Lender by the jurisdiction under the laws of which it is organized or is resident or carries on business through a permanent establishment located therein or any political subdivisions thereof). If a Credit Party shall be required by law to deduct any Taxes from or in respect of any sum payable hereunder or under the Notes (excluding Taxes imposed on or measured by the net income or capital of Lender by the jurisdiction under the laws of which it is organized or is resident or carries on business through a permanent establishment located therein or any political subdivisions thereof), (i) the sum payable shall be increased as much as shall be necessary so that, after making all required withholdings and deductions (including withholdings and deductions applicable to additional sums payable under this ), Lender receives an amount equal to the sum it would have received had no such withholdings or deductions been made, (ii) the applicable Credit Party shall make such deductions, and (iii) the applicable Credit Party shall pay the full amount deducted to the relevant taxing or other authority in accordance with applicable law. Within 30 days after the date of any payment of Taxes, Borrower shall furnish to Lender the original or a certified copy of a receipt evidencing payment thereof.
